description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for a career in Critical Care Nursing? If you are seeking an opportunity to join a progressive unit to further your critical care education and experience then please read on as Sandwell &amp; West Birmingham NHS Trust wants to invest in you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Critical Care department within the Sandwell &amp; West Birmingham NHS Trust admits in the region of 1400 patients a year and the flexible utilization of beds allows for a dynamic flow through the patients Critical Care pathway. Moving forward The Trust are entering an exciting chapter, Midland Metropolitan Hospital will open in 2022 and will provide the highest quality acute specialist services in a purpose built facility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a, committed and enthusiastic Band 5 nurse to join our team. This post is an excellent opportunity for a nurse to acquire knowledge and skills in the sphere of critical care services. If you are looking for an opportunity to enhance and develop within a positive and challenging environment, then this may be the role for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supported by an enthusiastic and dynamic senior leadership team, the unit is responsive to specialist modernization programs at local network and national network levels. We offer an established induction program over 12 months, supported by our practice development team and critical care staff. We also actively encourage your professional and personal development, offering opportunities to access post graduate education including “Adult Critical Care Nursing Course” within the local university.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NOTE: Due to the current Covid 19 pandemic, all interviews will be conducted virtually. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
